        // Call your method here
    }
}, 5000); // 5 seconds delay
```
This will call the `run()` method after a 5-second delay, which in turn calls your desired method.

Alternatively, you can use the `Timer` class or third-party libraries like `RxJava` or `Guava`. But for simple delayed method calls, `Handler` is usually the way to go.

One thing to keep in mind is that if you're calling this from the UI thread, you might want to consider using a `Runnable` with a `Looper` instead of directly posting a delay. This can help prevent any potential issues with the UI thread being blocked.

Also, if you need more control over the timing or want to cancel the delayed call, you might want to look into using a `TimerTask` or a similar approach.

