Filtering a Java Collection can be achieved in several ways, depending on your specific requirements and the type of collection you're working with. 

If you're using Java 8, I'd recommend using the `stream()` method to create a Stream from your Collection. This allows you to use the `filter()` method to apply a predicate to each element in the stream. Here's an example:

```java
Collection<MyObject> collection = ...;
Predicate<MyObject> predicate = ...;

Stream<MyObject> stream = collection.stream();
stream.filter(predicate).collect(Collectors.toList());
```

This will create a new List containing only the elements that match the predicate.

If you're not using Java 8, or if you prefer not to use streams, you can use the `removeIf()` method on the Collection itself. This will modify the original collection by removing all elements that don't match the predicate:

```java
